Moody&#8217;s said on Tuesday it would not, as expected, issue a sovereign credit rating decision on South Africa this Friday.Newly-appointed Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba on Tuesday once again tried to calm waters saying that the changes in executive did not mean a change in fiscal policy. He said the National Treasury was a strong institution. He was speaking after the Pravin Gordhan formally handed to him.On Monday S&amp;P downgraded SA to so-called junk status.Moody&#8217;s announced that it had placed South Africa on a review for a downgrade after a cabinet reshuffle.Moody&#8217;s places SA&#8217;s sovereign at two notches above non-investment grade at Baa2.